title: Contemporary British Painting (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Contemporary British Painting
Frederick A. Praeger, Inc. | 1968 | ISBN: N/A | English | 162 pages | PDF | 18 MB


Painting in Britain today, as in America, has great vitality and diversity. Pop, op, hard-edge, and shaped painting all have innovators and practitioners in England. The works in Contemporary British Painting were selected, under the sponsorship of the Peter Stuyvesant Foundation, to illustrate the main tendencies in British painting since the late 1950's. Alan Bowness' Introduction sets the present activity in a perspective of the entire twentieth century
